About 1913.

620 Park Avenue, at N. W. corner of 65th Street, a new apartment
building nearing completion.
It replaces the old 7-story Palacio apartments.
Early 1924.

NNG ~3788

Park Avenue, east side, south from E. 67th to 65th Streets, and showing prominently the Seventh Regiment Armory occupying the 67th -66th Street frontage. This structure, built in 1878-80 formerly had a pointed steeple where the flag is flying.. The photographer is viewing same from a similar vantage point in both instances (S.W. corner of Park Avenue and 88th Street) and shows the changed railing used in fencing the center plot dividing the traffic lanes.
June 8, 1928.
View 2: April 25, 1938.
P.L. Sperr
